CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1783646288
OL,3,CClimate change pushing wading bird to
OL,4,Cbrink in UK as numbers fall 89% `
OL,5,Cexperts
OL,7,FThe UK could lose its first bird
OL,8,Fspecies to climate change,
OL,9,Fconservationists have warned, as
OL,10,Fmountain-breeding dotterel numbers
OL,11,Ftumbled almost 90%.
OL,13,FThe small, wading birds with rusty-
OL,14,Forange chests migrate from northern
OL,15,FAfrica to mountainous regions in the
OL,16,FUK each summer to breed, and are
OL,17,Fadapted to rearing their young in
OL,18,Frocky plateaus and sparse vegetation
OL,19,Fin those environments.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1783646288
OL,3,CClimate change pushing wading bird to
OL,4,Cbrink in UK as numbers fall 89% `
OL,5,Cexperts
OL,7,FBut monitoring has shown dotterels
OL,8,Fhave suffered significant reductions
OL,9,Fin both their range and population
OL,10,Fsizes.
OL,12,FThe latest, national, dotterel survey
OL,13,Fhas seen numbers fall 89% since
OL,14,Fmonitoring began in 1988, with
OL,15,Fdeclines increasing since the 2011
OL,16,Fsurvey, while most of the remaining
OL,17,Fpopulation is now restricted to the
OL,18,Feastern and northern Highlands of
OL,19,FScotland, conservationists said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1783646288
OL,3,CClimate change pushing wading bird to
OL,4,Cbrink in UK as numbers fall 89% `
OL,5,Cexperts
OL,7,FWith declines mirrored within
OL,8,Fprotected areas, where the birds might
OL,9,Fbe expected to be safe from other
OL,10,Fthreats, the conservationists warn
OL,11,Fthat climate change could be one of
OL,12,Fthe potential causes of decline.
OL,14,FSpecies which depend on mountainous
OL,15,Fhabitats are particularly vulnerable
OL,16,Fto climate change, as hotter and drier
OL,17,Ftemperatures push them higher and
OL,18,Fhigher up in the landscape until they
OL,19,Fhave nowhere left to go, they warn.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1783646288
OL,3,CClimate change pushing wading bird to
OL,4,Cbrink in UK as numbers fall 89% `
OL,5,Cexperts
OL,7,FDotterels breed in mountain ranges
OL,8,Facross northern Europe and Asia, and
OL,9,Fthe global population is classed as
OL,10,F"least concern" over their extinction
OL,11,Frisk on the IUCN Red List.
OL,13,FBut the team behind the survey say it
OL,14,Fcould be the first time the UK has
OL,15,Fdocumented a species being driven
OL,16,Ftowards extinction locally as a result
OL,17,Fof climate change.
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@OO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1783646288
OL,3,CClimate change pushing wading bird to
OL,4,Cbrink in UK as numbers fall 89% `
OL,5,Cexperts
OL,7,FDr Leah Kelly, RSPB conservation
OL,8,Fscientist and one of key scientists on
OL,9,Fthe project, said: "Dotterel are in
OL,10,Fsteep decline, and we are seeing them
OL,11,Fdisappearing before our very eyes.
OL,13,F"The fact they need mountain tops to
OL,14,Fbreed has made them particularly
OL,15,Fsusceptible to habitat loss as climate
OL,16,Fchange alters their montane
OL,17,Fenvironment."
OL,26,@qD@TOUuD@AOUyD@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1783646288
OL,3,CClimate change pushing wading bird to
OL,4,Cbrink in UK as numbers fall 89% `
OL,5,Cexperts
OL,7,FThe latest survey was carried out in
OL,8,F2025, with three, previous, national,
OL,9,Fdotterel surveys in 1988, 1999 and
OL,10,F2011 revealing "worrying" contractions
OL,11,Fin the bird's range and a 57% fall in
OL,12,Fnumbers between 1988 and 2011.
OL,14,FThe 2025 assessment, led by the RSPB,
OL,15,Faimed to find out if the losses `
OL,16,Fwhich had led to the dotterel being
OL,17,F"red listed" on the UK's birds of
OL,18,Fconservation concern list ` were
OL,19,Fcontinuing and where breeding pairs
OL,20,Fremained in the UK.
OL,26,@rD@POUrD@YO]yD@AOUyD@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1783646288
OL,3,CClimate change pushing wading bird to
OL,4,Cbrink in UK as numbers fall 89% `
OL,5,Cexperts
OL,7,FWith males, unusually, staying on the
OL,8,Fnest to incubate the eggs, the survey
OL,9,Fused sightings of male dotterels to
OL,10,Festimate the size of the breeding
OL,11,Fpopulation.
OL,13,FJust 22 (10%) of the 217 sites
OL,14,Fsurveyed contained any breeding males,
OL,15,Fwith no breeding dotterels discovered
OL,16,Fin England, Wales or southern Scotland.
OL,18,FJust 33 males were recorded in the
OL,19,Fsurvey, leading conservationists to
OL,20,Festimate a total of 112 breeding males
OL,21,Facross the UK.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1783646288
OL,3,CClimate change pushing wading bird to
OL,4,Cbrink in UK as numbers fall 89% `
OL,5,Cexperts
OL,7,FNumbers had fallen by almost three
OL,8,Fquarters (74%) since the 2011 survey
OL,9,Fand a similar rate of decline was seen
OL,10,Finside and outside "special protected
OL,11,Fareas" ` suggesting the main cause of
OL,12,Ftumbling populations was the same
OL,13,Facross all mountain areas, the team
OL,14,Fsaid.
OL,26,@rD@TOUsD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1783646288
OL,3,CClimate change pushing wading bird to
OL,4,Cbrink in UK as numbers fall 89% `
OL,5,Cexperts
OL,7,FThey said climate change, in
OL,8,Fcombination with overgrazing, degrades
OL,9,Fthe low-growing, alpine vegetation the
OL,10,Fdotterels favour, while their
OL,11,Fpreferred food of cranefly larvae also
OL,12,Fappears to have undergone declines in
OL,13,FUK mountain sites.
OL,15,FWhile dotterels could soon be lost
OL,16,Ffrom the UK, there is a chance to keep
OL,17,Fthem here as a breeding bird by
OL,18,Fmanaging grazing to keep habitats in
OL,19,Fgood condition and reducing
OL,20,Fdisturbance by hillwalkers and dogs,
OL,21,Fthe experts said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1783646288
OL,3,CClimate change pushing wading bird to
OL,4,Cbrink in UK as numbers fall 89% `
OL,5,Cexperts
OL,7,FNatureScot ornithologist, Dr Nicola
OL,8,FLargey, said: "The striking dotterel
OL,9,Fhas long been a special sight for
OL,10,Fthose who spend time in Scotland's
OL,11,Fuplands and mountains, but sadly the
OL,12,Fevidence shows the species is now in
OL,13,Fprecipitous decline.
OL,15,F"The potential loss of this
OL,16,Fdistinctive bird from our hills
OL,17,Fdemonstrates the urgent need to tackle
OL,18,Fthe twin crises of climate change and
OL,19,Fbiodiversity loss that are threatening
OL,20,Four wildlife and the habitats they
OL,21,Fdepend on.
OL,26,@pD@OOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30511
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1783646288
OL,3,CClimate change pushing wading bird to
OL,4,Cbrink in UK as numbers fall 89% `
OL,5,Cexperts
OL,7,F"At a local level, managing pressures
OL,8,Fon dotterel habitat such as
OL,9,Fovergrazing can give us the best
OL,10,Fchance to retain them."
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/11
